WEBVTT

00:08.774 --> 00:12.345
-* Feliz Navidad *
-(laughter)

00:12.478 --> 00:13.679
* Feliz Navidad... *

00:13.813 --> 00:14.980
I don't know, Jake.

00:15.115 --> 00:17.350
There's got to be some girl
you like.

00:17.483 --> 00:19.852
* Prospero aÃ±o y felicidad... *

00:19.985 --> 00:22.122
The girl in the purple--
she's kind of cute.

00:22.222 --> 00:25.791
Oh. I think she used to work
at the White House

00:25.891 --> 00:28.194
a couple years ago.

00:29.729 --> 00:31.364
Yeah?

00:31.497 --> 00:33.199
Yeah.

00:35.168 --> 00:36.502
Good luck.

00:36.636 --> 00:38.504
Um...

00:38.638 --> 00:41.207
I've been trying to give off
an air of unapproachability.

00:41.341 --> 00:42.308
-Mm.
-Was I successful?

00:42.408 --> 00:43.976
Oh, yes. Good job.

00:44.076 --> 00:46.045
-Good. Good.
-(laughs)

00:46.212 --> 00:47.413
I'm Jake.
Jake Tapper.

00:47.547 --> 00:49.582
-I'm Monica.
-Can I, uh,

00:49.715 --> 00:51.050
buy you a drink?

00:51.184 --> 00:52.652
Oh, you know,
it's-it's a weeknight.

00:52.752 --> 00:54.187
I was gonna head home
and have dinner.

00:54.320 --> 00:56.189
You know they have food here.

00:56.322 --> 00:57.590
It's, uh... it's Tex-Mex.

00:57.723 --> 00:59.359
It's world-famous
Washington, D.C. Tex-Mex.

01:00.693 --> 01:02.562
Sure.

01:02.695 --> 01:04.029
On long-haul flights,

01:04.164 --> 01:05.765
the secretary of defense
does press avails,

01:05.898 --> 01:07.567
and then, they all get
to go to sleep,

01:07.700 --> 01:10.069
and I stay up through the night
transcribing every word.

01:10.203 --> 01:11.204
That sounds fun.

01:11.337 --> 01:12.738
It's a spelling minefield.

01:12.905 --> 01:15.175
The Chernomyrdins
and the Khmelnytskys.

01:15.275 --> 01:17.009
I mean, you go east of Austria,

01:17.109 --> 01:19.879
and the vowels are just never
where you expect them to be.

01:20.012 --> 01:21.414
Plus, I'm a shit typist, so...

01:21.581 --> 01:22.748
(laughs)

01:22.882 --> 01:24.584
But, um,
talking about it now, I...

01:24.717 --> 01:28.688
I've been sort of myopic
this past year,

01:28.788 --> 01:31.691
and... I really look at it.

01:31.791 --> 01:33.393
This job's actually been
kind of neat.

01:33.526 --> 01:36.061
-Mm.
-Yeah, I'm actually... I'm...

01:36.196 --> 01:38.063
I'm moving soon.
I have a job interview

01:38.198 --> 01:41.267
-in New York on... on Friday.
-Ah.

01:41.401 --> 01:44.304
What did you mean--
you've been myopic?

01:44.437 --> 01:47.240
I don't know. I just...

01:47.373 --> 01:50.410
I guess I've been a bit
of a D.C. zombie.

01:50.543 --> 01:52.044
Hmm.

01:52.144 --> 01:53.879
And I'm... I'm ready to wake up.

01:53.979 --> 01:56.249
-Oh. Thank you.
-Thank you.

01:56.382 --> 01:58.117
-We're gonna split that.
-No, no, no.

01:58.251 --> 01:59.952
-Yes.
-This is a date.

02:03.256 --> 02:05.458
(distant phones ringing)

02:15.000 --> 02:16.902
(footsteps approaching)

02:17.002 --> 02:18.804
MONICA:
Hey, Linda.

02:18.971 --> 02:20.506
What to watch me fix the Xerox
for the 20th time

02:20.640 --> 02:22.141
-this week?
-Oh. No.

02:22.308 --> 02:24.176
-(laughs)
-Oh, wait.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.646
-Are these the invitations?
-Yes.

02:26.779 --> 02:28.013
Ah.

02:28.147 --> 02:29.815
You can help me hand them out.

02:30.816 --> 02:33.018
God. How did you afford these?

02:33.152 --> 02:35.821
Oh. Well, I go nuts
for Christmas.

02:35.988 --> 02:37.590
I know
it's maybe not your thing.

02:37.690 --> 02:39.592
Oh, please. We're L.A. Jews.

02:39.692 --> 02:41.627
I've been going to Christmas
parties since I was born.

02:41.761 --> 02:43.629
You can come, right?

02:43.763 --> 02:45.265
When do you go up
for your interview?

02:45.365 --> 02:46.599
Thursday. I'm a wreck.

02:46.699 --> 02:48.268
You'll do great.

02:48.368 --> 02:50.803
Ugh. After Revlon,
we're going to 21 with basically

02:50.936 --> 02:53.306
my entire extended family,
and I have to look nice.

02:53.439 --> 02:55.308
My family's a whole thing.

02:55.441 --> 02:57.109
So I think I'm gonna wear
that navy dress I showed you.

02:57.209 --> 02:58.611
You got it cleaned?

02:58.711 --> 03:00.846
Oh, no, not yet,
but I will before I go.

03:00.980 --> 03:03.683
Oh. Merry Christmas.

03:03.816 --> 03:05.685
LUCIANNE:
How'd the girl take the news?

03:05.818 --> 03:07.853
Oh. I still haven't told her
about the subpoena.

03:08.020 --> 03:09.855
-You haven't? Why?
-I know.

03:10.022 --> 03:12.858
If she doesn't hear it from you,
she's going to get suspicious.

03:12.992 --> 03:14.827
Yes, I realize that.
I'm going to tell her.

03:14.960 --> 03:16.028
That-That's not even
why I called.

03:16.195 --> 03:18.498
She's gonna get
the dress cleaned.

03:18.631 --> 03:19.532
-What?
-She wants

03:19.665 --> 03:21.301
-to wear it.
-That stain is

03:21.401 --> 03:23.035
white gold.

03:23.168 --> 03:25.705
It proves what she says
on your tapes really happened.

03:25.838 --> 03:27.707
Ugh.

03:27.840 --> 03:29.742
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

03:29.875 --> 03:31.877
It can absolutely be used
to match DNA,

03:32.011 --> 03:33.313
even years later.

03:33.413 --> 03:35.315
(sighs)
Really?

03:35.415 --> 03:38.984
You get her on the horn
right now, and you stop her!

03:39.084 --> 03:41.153
(phone beeps)

03:48.528 --> 03:51.364
-I need a minute.
-Uh, yeah, this is
your favorite thing,

03:51.497 --> 03:53.566
-and you had us stay home
for a night.
-I just, I have to do a call.

03:53.699 --> 03:54.767
Just need a minute.

03:57.870 --> 03:59.939
(Allison scoffs softly)

04:01.407 --> 04:03.409
(line ringing)

04:09.515 --> 04:11.451
-Hello?
-LINDA: Hi.

04:11.584 --> 04:12.752
How are you?

04:12.918 --> 04:14.720
Fine. I'm tired.
I just got off the treadmill.

04:14.854 --> 04:16.088
LINDA:
You're so good.

04:16.255 --> 04:17.590
-(laughs)
-Listen.

04:17.723 --> 04:19.725
I wanted to say to you--
and you can do

04:19.859 --> 04:22.528
what you want with this--
but the blue dress.

04:22.628 --> 04:24.964
I don't think you should
wear that to your interview.

04:25.097 --> 04:26.932
-Why?
-Call me crazy, but

04:27.066 --> 04:29.735
I believe it would be smart
for you to keep that,

04:29.869 --> 04:34.106
uncleaned, in your possession
in case you ever need it years

04:34.239 --> 04:35.074
-from now.
-(laughs)

04:35.207 --> 04:36.442
What?

04:36.609 --> 04:37.943
You think I need to keep

04:38.077 --> 04:40.446
a dress with that on it
for years?

04:40.613 --> 04:43.248
Okay, instead of always just
dissing what I say,

04:43.383 --> 04:45.551
listen.

04:45.651 --> 04:47.953
My cousin is a genetic...

04:48.120 --> 04:49.989
whatchamacallit.

04:50.122 --> 04:52.958
And during O.J. Simpson,
I was hooked on the trial.

04:53.092 --> 04:54.827
It was fabulous,
but all the

04:54.960 --> 04:57.296
DNA was Greek to me,
so I asked him about it.

04:57.463 --> 04:59.298
And he told me

04:59.465 --> 05:02.101
that an old crusty bit of semen
can be matched

05:02.234 --> 05:04.637
to a man's identity,
even ages later.

05:04.770 --> 05:07.507
But why would I care if it could
be matched to his identity?

05:07.640 --> 05:09.442
If you were ever to need proof.

05:09.575 --> 05:11.477
But I'm never going
to come forward about this.

05:11.611 --> 05:13.646
(laughing):
I'm not saying you would ever.

05:13.779 --> 05:16.315
And if anyone else did,
I would deny, deny, deny.

05:16.482 --> 05:18.951
I know. I know that, but just

05:19.084 --> 05:20.686
-do this...
-(sighs)

05:20.820 --> 05:22.955
for your own ultimate
protection,

05:23.088 --> 05:24.123
which-- mea culpa--

05:24.256 --> 05:26.091
I hope you never need it.

05:27.159 --> 05:29.595
I would say this
to my own daughter.

05:30.663 --> 05:31.997
Hello?

05:32.164 --> 05:33.666
Look, I want to feel confident
at the interview,

05:33.799 --> 05:35.334
and I know I look good
in that dress.

05:37.369 --> 05:40.440
(laughs):
Well, I mean...

05:40.540 --> 05:42.842
If you think it's flattering,
I mean, that's what matters.

05:42.975 --> 05:45.177
What?

05:45.310 --> 05:47.847
I want you to look thin
and beautiful.

05:48.013 --> 05:50.282
-What does that mean?
-(scoffs)

05:50.382 --> 05:53.519
I'm sorry,
but I would want to be told.

05:53.653 --> 05:55.521
The truth is,
you look heavy in that dress.

05:55.655 --> 05:57.523
Are you serious?

05:57.657 --> 05:59.725
(TV plays quietly)

05:59.859 --> 06:01.694
Okay, well...
well, what's more slimming--

06:01.827 --> 06:04.697
the peach suit,
or the... or the dark teal?

06:04.864 --> 06:07.667
Your peach suit is exquisite.

06:07.800 --> 06:11.236
I think that works beautifully.

06:22.181 --> 06:24.183
*

06:44.003 --> 06:46.071
(sighs)

06:48.007 --> 06:49.909
(Starr humming
"O Little Town of Bethlehem")

06:50.042 --> 06:51.343
(elevator bell dings)

06:51.443 --> 06:54.113
-(humming continues)
-Good morning, Judge Starr.

06:54.246 --> 06:56.015
Hmm.
Good morning, Neille.

06:56.115 --> 06:58.417
They're in there
waiting for you.

06:59.885 --> 07:01.921
This is not going
to be pleasant.

07:02.087 --> 07:03.623
Mm-hmm.

07:07.226 --> 07:09.428
Morning.
Sorry I'm late.

07:13.398 --> 07:16.636
I wanted to read a verse,
if I may.

07:19.572 --> 07:23.809
"We are persecuted,
but not forsaken by God;

07:23.943 --> 07:26.946
cast down, but not destroyed."

07:27.112 --> 07:28.981
Corinthians,
chapter four, verse nine.

07:29.114 --> 07:30.750
That's a prayer
for the defeated.

07:30.883 --> 07:32.918
No one in this room
should feel defeated.

07:33.052 --> 07:36.989
Now, I've asked Paul to take
every piece of evidence we have

07:37.122 --> 07:39.124
on President Clinton
and Whitewater,

07:39.291 --> 07:41.060
and put it all
into one document

07:41.160 --> 07:42.995
so we can take a look
and decide,

07:43.128 --> 07:45.631
do we have enough
to recommend impeachment.

07:45.765 --> 07:47.767
No.
Not-not today, not yet.

07:47.900 --> 07:49.401
But we're close.

07:49.501 --> 07:50.736
This doesn't say to me
it's time to shut down.

07:50.836 --> 07:52.137
This says keep going.

07:52.271 --> 07:54.139
Oh, Jackie,
it's been four years.

07:54.273 --> 07:55.775
We've exhausted
all of our leads.

07:55.908 --> 07:58.110
Bill Clinton committed
loan fraud when he was governor,

07:58.243 --> 08:00.145
and then he lied
about it under oath.

08:00.312 --> 08:02.147
We're just one witness short
of proving that.

08:02.314 --> 08:04.316
Every potential crime
is one witness short.

08:04.483 --> 08:06.118
What'd you just say?

08:06.251 --> 08:08.821
I said we don't have it.
Do you think

08:08.954 --> 08:10.155
I don't feel
like a failure, too?

08:10.289 --> 08:11.591
We're failures if we quit.

08:11.691 --> 08:13.358
What am I...
the only one who sees this? Huh?

08:13.492 --> 08:15.427
Come on.
Kavanaugh, huh?

08:15.527 --> 08:16.829
You don't think
we should just quit?

08:16.996 --> 08:19.331
I never like to take "no"
for an answer,

08:19.464 --> 08:21.867
but, Jackie, there isn't
a path forward here.

08:22.001 --> 08:24.837
Oh, great. Okay,
so you all want to fucking fold.

08:25.004 --> 08:27.339
-Jackie, please.
-I'm sorry, Judge.

08:30.475 --> 08:33.779
I look around this room,
and I see success.

08:33.879 --> 08:35.881
They said we were
on a partisan witch hunt,

08:36.015 --> 08:37.650
but we found real wrongdoing.

08:37.783 --> 08:41.854
Because of us, the governor
of Arkansas had to resign,

08:42.021 --> 08:44.323
and we achieved 12 convictions

08:44.456 --> 08:46.291
of other people
around the Clintons.

08:46.391 --> 08:48.828
Yeah, but none of whom
would flip on Bill or Hillary.

08:48.961 --> 08:50.562
No, that didn't happen,

08:50.696 --> 08:52.364
and there's no indication
that's going to change,

08:52.497 --> 08:53.866
and that's our problem.

08:54.033 --> 08:57.737
Oh, Judge, you can't sit there
after all this time

08:57.870 --> 08:59.538
and tell me
that they're not guilty.

08:59.705 --> 09:02.041
In fact, I'll sit here
and tell you candidly

09:02.174 --> 09:05.010
that I believe President Clinton
is guilty as sin.

09:05.144 --> 09:07.412
Even worse,
I believe, he actively

09:07.546 --> 09:11.383
blocked people from cooperating
in this investigation.

09:11.516 --> 09:14.553
Now, I can believe that
and you can believe that,

09:14.720 --> 09:17.556
but it doesn't matter
what we believe.

09:17.723 --> 09:19.759
It matters what we can prove.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.397
Let's put it to a vote.

09:25.530 --> 09:28.267
Does anyone here feel
we have the goods

09:28.400 --> 09:30.169
to take this to the Hill

09:30.269 --> 09:33.706
and recommend the impeachment
of President Clinton?

09:45.417 --> 09:46.919
ASSOCIATE:
All right, Mr. President.

09:47.052 --> 09:49.588
Let's move on to a different
line of questioning.

09:49.755 --> 09:52.892
In 1987, you repeatedly visited
the home of Beth Coulson,

09:53.025 --> 09:54.927
always while
her husband was away.

09:55.060 --> 09:57.930
Was the purpose of these visits
to have sex with Beth Coulson?

09:58.063 --> 09:59.464
No, it was not.

09:59.598 --> 10:02.735
So you just happened to only
visit her when she was alone?

10:02.868 --> 10:04.269
Are you asking me a question?

10:04.403 --> 10:06.271
Yes. Do you honestly
expect us to believe

10:06.405 --> 10:07.907
that that was not
a sexual relationship?

10:08.040 --> 10:09.608
I told you before,
we were just friends.

10:09.742 --> 10:11.711
Let's move on
to Marilyn Jo Jenkins.

10:11.811 --> 10:14.113
Is it true that you met with her
four times in your private

10:14.246 --> 10:15.480
basement office at
the Arkansas Governor's Mansion?

10:15.614 --> 10:17.116
Fuck this.

10:17.249 --> 10:19.451
Mr. President, this is what

10:19.584 --> 10:20.920
they're going to do to you.

10:21.053 --> 10:22.454
Yeah, this is horseshit.
You should be making a list

10:22.587 --> 10:24.056
like this for Paula Jones.

10:24.156 --> 10:26.125
We are. When she sits
for her deposition

10:26.291 --> 10:27.927
next week,
she won't know what hit her.

10:28.060 --> 10:31.096
But right after that,
you're up, under oath.

10:31.230 --> 10:32.798
We can't delay it anymore.

10:32.932 --> 10:34.666
No. I bet you Kennedy didn't
have to answer this shit.

10:34.800 --> 10:36.769
Yeah, well, that was the '60s.

10:36.902 --> 10:38.771
Excuse me.

10:38.904 --> 10:40.840
What did you say?

10:41.907 --> 10:44.276
Just that...
that that was the '60s.

10:46.245 --> 10:48.080
Ti-Times are changing.

10:48.180 --> 10:49.614
For women.

10:49.749 --> 10:52.752
You know how many women
I have in my cabinet?

10:52.852 --> 10:54.954
Not... off the top of...

10:55.087 --> 10:56.521
I mean, there's, um...

10:56.655 --> 11:00.826
Janet Reno,
first female attorney general.

11:00.960 --> 11:03.963
Madeleine Albright, first female
secretary of state.

11:04.096 --> 11:08.333
Donna Shalala, secretary
of Health and Human Services.

11:08.500 --> 11:10.836
Alexis Herman,
secretary of Labor.

11:11.003 --> 11:13.005
Carol Browner, EPA.

11:13.172 --> 11:14.639
Aida Alvarez, SBA.

11:14.774 --> 11:17.176
Charlene Barshefsky,
U.S. trade rep.

11:17.342 --> 11:20.679
Janet Yellen, chair of the
Council of Economic Advisors.

11:20.813 --> 11:24.183
No one supports women
more than me.

11:29.288 --> 11:30.655
(clears throat)

11:30.790 --> 11:32.391
(door slams)

11:34.359 --> 11:35.861
(phone receiver clicks)

11:36.028 --> 11:37.797
(dialing)

11:41.466 --> 11:43.335
(line ringing)

11:43.468 --> 11:45.537
(sighs)

11:45.670 --> 11:47.706
(phone ringing)

11:51.844 --> 11:53.145
Hello?

11:53.245 --> 11:55.547
Hey. Did I wake you?

11:55.680 --> 11:57.749
No.

11:57.883 --> 12:00.352
No. It's fine.
I was awake.

12:01.320 --> 12:02.855
How you doing?

12:02.988 --> 12:04.689
Um, I'm good.

12:04.824 --> 12:06.892
I went to New York
for my Revlon interview,

12:07.026 --> 12:08.560
and they basically
offered me the job.

12:08.693 --> 12:10.863
Oh, that's great.
Good job.

12:10.996 --> 12:13.365
What's wrong?

12:15.567 --> 12:19.571
I just wanted to tell you, um...

12:19.738 --> 12:23.242
I saw the witness list
for the Paula Jones suit,

12:23.408 --> 12:25.210
and your name is on it.

12:25.344 --> 12:26.578
What?

12:26.745 --> 12:28.380
It's-it's not a big deal.

12:28.513 --> 12:30.549
It just broke my heart a little
to see you there.

12:30.682 --> 12:32.251
Wait.
Paula Jones.

12:32.384 --> 12:34.286
Why would I be on the witness
list? What does that mean?

12:34.419 --> 12:36.021
Oh, it doesn't mean anything.

12:36.121 --> 12:37.422
You know,
this thing is pretty much

12:37.589 --> 12:39.191
every woman I've ever talked to.

12:39.291 --> 12:41.126
But we've more than talked.

12:42.694 --> 12:45.430
You know, you-you probably
won't even get a subpoena.

12:45.564 --> 12:47.632
Okay, okay, well,
but what if I do?

12:47.766 --> 12:49.634
Well, for something like this,
you know,

12:49.768 --> 12:52.271
you probably wouldn't even
have to show up

12:52.404 --> 12:53.772
in person.

12:53.906 --> 12:56.075
You just get a lawyer
to draft an affidavit.

12:56.208 --> 12:58.743
-Saying what?
-Well, Monica...

13:00.412 --> 13:01.947
...what would you want to say?

13:06.285 --> 13:08.787
(quietly):
Uh...

13:08.954 --> 13:11.223
I would say that nothing
ever happened between us.

13:16.061 --> 13:19.631
If anything happens...

13:19.764 --> 13:21.800
you can call Betty.

13:23.268 --> 13:24.970
Okay.

13:25.104 --> 13:27.139
Thank you.

13:28.107 --> 13:29.975
Can I just ask?

13:30.142 --> 13:32.477
This lawsuit has caused
so much trouble for you.

13:32.644 --> 13:34.313
Why don't you just
try to settle it again?

13:34.479 --> 13:35.948
Well...

13:37.917 --> 13:39.651
It's complicated.

13:39.784 --> 13:43.688
(sighs heavily)

13:43.822 --> 13:45.490
-I mean,
I think this is charming.
-(sighs)

13:45.624 --> 13:47.159
Okay, I don't understand what's
supposed to fit on this plate.

13:47.326 --> 13:49.194
-Cookies, Monica.
-Like what?

13:49.328 --> 13:50.996
-One single cookie?
-Ugh.

13:51.130 --> 13:52.998
It's about creating
a festive ambience,

13:53.132 --> 13:55.000
not the utility of the plate.

13:55.134 --> 13:58.270
Sorry. I really don't mean
to be a drag. I just...

13:58.370 --> 14:01.373
I can't stop thinking
about my name on that list.

14:01.506 --> 14:04.977
Well, it sounded like he wasn't
especially concerned, so...

14:05.110 --> 14:07.512
He says that I probably
won't get a subpoena,

14:07.679 --> 14:09.348
but what if I do?

14:09.514 --> 14:12.184
I mean, I would have to answer
questions about him under oath.

14:12.317 --> 14:14.019
It's unthinkable.

14:15.887 --> 14:17.889
I got a subpoena.

14:20.125 --> 14:22.327
I've been meaning to mention it.
It's just...

