-Linda, do you understand

35:16.714 --> 35:18.282
how much trouble you're in?

35:18.416 --> 35:20.484
If these tapes are introduced
into evidence,

35:20.618 --> 35:23.120
you will be prosecuted,
you could go to jail.

35:23.287 --> 35:24.455
(gasps)

35:24.622 --> 35:27.124
You said taping phone calls
was entirely fine.

35:27.291 --> 35:28.492
LUCIANNE:
Well, it is in New York.

35:28.626 --> 35:30.127
Well, not everyone lives
in New York.

35:30.261 --> 35:31.929
(laughing):
Yes, I never understand that.

35:32.062 --> 35:33.497
This is serious.

35:33.631 --> 35:35.299
I could go to prison.

35:35.466 --> 35:37.901
-I could lose everything.
-Okay.

35:38.001 --> 35:40.304
What does your lawyer say to do?

35:40.471 --> 35:42.606
He wants to tell Bob Bennett
about the tapes.

35:42.740 --> 35:44.308
What?

35:44.442 --> 35:47.077
So he'll settle,
so they won't come to light.

35:47.177 --> 35:49.613
If this case gets killed,
he gets away with all of it.

35:49.747 --> 35:51.649
I don't want that, either,

35:51.782 --> 35:55.152
but Maryland has a Democrat for
governor and attorney general.

35:55.319 --> 35:58.121
The White House will have no
trouble sending them after me.

35:58.256 --> 35:59.657
Maximum sentence.

35:59.823 --> 36:02.025
Linda, calm down.
We just need to figure out a way

36:02.159 --> 36:04.262
to get you immunity
from prosecution.

36:04.362 --> 36:05.863
How are we gonna do that?

36:05.996 --> 36:08.131
I have an idea.
Let me get my Rolodex.

36:08.266 --> 36:10.468
(sighs)

36:12.002 --> 36:13.637
(phone ringing)

36:13.771 --> 36:15.339
Conway.

36:15.473 --> 36:16.507
Do you have connections

36:16.640 --> 36:18.509
-to Ken Starr's office?
-Of course I do.

36:18.642 --> 36:21.512
We need to make them aware of
Linda Tripp as fast as we can.

36:21.645 --> 36:23.046
(knocking)

36:26.183 --> 36:27.351
Hey, stranger.

36:27.518 --> 36:29.052
-MONICA: Hey.
-(door closes)

36:29.186 --> 36:30.854
(Monica sighs)

36:30.988 --> 36:32.656
When's the big move?

36:34.024 --> 36:35.993
Next week.

36:36.126 --> 36:37.194
You okay?

36:37.361 --> 36:39.363
Yeah.

36:39.497 --> 36:40.831
Yeah.
No, I'm fine.

36:40.964 --> 36:43.534
I got you a few things.

36:44.735 --> 36:48.171
For the new New Yorker.

36:52.876 --> 36:55.078
Wow.
That's, um...

36:55.212 --> 36:57.247
That's very sweet.
Thank you, but I, um...

36:57.381 --> 36:59.383
Hold on.
We're not done.

37:00.518 --> 37:03.554
Oh, my God.
I love him, um,

37:03.687 --> 37:06.424
-but I...
-And the last

37:06.557 --> 37:08.225
but not least.

37:14.898 --> 37:17.601
I found this in Vancouver

37:17.735 --> 37:20.371
in a First Nation store.

37:20.504 --> 37:22.773
You know,
a bear symbolizes courage.

37:22.906 --> 37:27.411
So in your new life up there
in the big city,

37:27.578 --> 37:31.181
when you need to be strong,
just hold him close.

37:32.683 --> 37:34.251
You okay?

37:34.418 --> 37:36.253
I... I...

37:36.420 --> 37:38.255
I love them.

37:38.422 --> 37:40.391
Really, I love them,
but I can't take them.

37:40.524 --> 37:42.393
